<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-JEFFERSON-COLUMN26-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COMMENTARY: E-mail to Gates: I feel your pain
 &HT;    By Stebbins Jefferson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Each morning when I read the newspaper, I look to the comics for
a bit of humor to jump-start my day. One day this week, however, I
found the best laugh in the Business section. There, I learned that
Bill Gates, the nation's richest man, has a lot in common with the
average computer dummy.
</P>
<P>
   Mr. Gates is fighting an antitrust case. Like the rest of us,
he's finding out that e-mail is an unforgiving convenience.
</P>
<P>
   The Justice Department and 20 states are suing Mr. Gates'
company, Microsoft. They claim that to eliminate competition in the
computer software business, Microsoft embedded Internet browser
software into each Windows operating system. Microsoft's
competitor, Netscape, needs to sell its browser for the company to
grow.
</P>
<P>
   In other words, Mr. Gates is accused of trying to create an
illegal monopoly to force out competitors. He denies it. Though
Netscape may have been hurt, he says, he's just trying to improve
his product and better serve consumers.
</P>
<P>
   The case seems to hinge on intent, not consequences. That's
where Mr. Gates' own electronic words _ he writes more than 100
e-mails a day _ could reveal more than he wants the court to know.
</P>
<P>
   In January 1996, for example, he messaged top aides that
``winning Internet browser market share is a very, very important
goal.'' When asked in court what he meant by that statement, he
said he couldn't remember. In fact, the Harvard dropout who hired
Harvard graduates and made them all millionaires has trouble
answering any questions related to e-mail. He can't remember what
he was thinking when he wrote the memo or what his words meant.
Alas, he can't even remember wriels for pre-teens.
</P>
<P>
   Now, that's what I'd call girl power.
</P>
<P>
   Mary McCarty writes for the Dayton Daily News, Dayton, Ohio.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clientsce
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-11-25-98 0936EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
