</P>
<P>
   By Mary Shelley. Edited, with an introduction, by Claire
Tomalin. Illustrated. 179 pp. New York: Alfred A. Knopf. $20. Not
long after 'Frankenstein,' Mary Shelley wrote this optimistic fairy
tale.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-RUM-NYTSF, THE RUM DIARY: The Long Lost Novel. By Hunter
S. Thompson. 204 pp. New York: Simon &AMP; Schuster. $24. Set in the
Caribbean, this first novel by a 22-year-old Hunter Thompson has
lots of sex and alcohol but no drugs yet.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-EAST-NYTSF, EAST INTO UPPER EAST, Plain Tales From New
York and New Delhi. By Ruth Prawer Jhabvala. 314 pp. Washington:
