</P>
<P>
   FOOD-PIES _ Though often in the shadows of cakes and other more
dazzling desserts, pies move into the spotlight for Thanksgiving.
So really, this is no time for stage fright. But if you are a pie
novice with a dough phobia, chances are you are going to try to
crib it with a store-bought crust. Rose Levy Beranbaum, author of
the newly released Pie and Pastry Bible, says fear not. She shows
us how to make a pie crust worthy of giving thanks for. (Walker,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
