<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-25 11:16 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8865 &Cx1f; tad-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CPT-E-SHOPPING-HOWTO-     11-25 0494
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CPT-E-SHOPPING-HOWTO-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;    EDITORS: RESENDING FOR THOSE WHO NEED IT
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 
 (Repeating as part of a weekly roundup of computer features)   &HT;    E-shopping's easy, can be fun
 &HT;    By Frances Katz
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   So you've seen the packed parking lots at the mall, you're sick
of staring at the piles of catalogs cluttering your kitchen table
and you've decided that electronic shopping is the only way to go.
Trouble is, you've never shopped online before. Fear not first-time
shoppers: If e-shopping was hard or scary, nobody would do it and
you wouldn't be able to order Gap sweat shirts online.
</P>
<P>
   You don't need much to hop on the e-shopping bandwagon, besides
a computer, a modem and an Internet browser.
</P>
<P>
   It's always smart to do a little Web comparison shopping to make
sure you're getting the best value for your money. Sites such as
Junglee (http://www.junglee.com) and BottomDollar
(http://www.bottomdollar.com) will be able to tell you which Web
shops are selling the object of your desire at the lowest price.
Many portal sites such as HotBot (http://www.hotbot.com) or Yahoo
(http://www.yahoo.com) and Snap (http://www.snap.com) also offer
bargain finders for various products. Also be on the lookout for
free shipping, gift wrapping and other incentives to give your
business to one site instead of another. For example, music store
CDNow (http://www.cdnow.com) recently had an online trivia contest
with $10 off any purchase as a prize. Also be sure to check
carefully the shipping time the Web site promises. While experience
shows that most ship dates are realistic, many sites may have
cutoff dates for holiday deliveries, so as the saying goes, shop
early and often.
</P>
<P>
   Most shopping Web sites, such as Amazon.com have made the
purchasing process fairly intuitive. There might be something to
click along the lines of ``Add to my shopping cart'' or more
bluntly ``buy this now.'' Don't panic if you change your mind,
you'll have several chances to take items out of your virtual
shopping basket. You can also cancel your order at any time in the
ordering process, but once you click ``submit'' you've placed your
order, so make sure you really want something before sending
anything off into cyberspace.
</P>
<P>
   Once you've ordered your items, remember to keep copies of all
correspondence. Most of it will be via e-mail, so keep copies or
print out the information and store it in a safe place. This will
give you confirmation numbers and will also let you know when to
expect your item.
</P>
<P>
   Most online shopping sites will stay in close contact with you
via e-mail, letting you know they've received your order and
letting you know when it's shipped. They also let you know how to
contact them if you have a problem. However, if you shop wisely,
you'll see online shopping is not only easy, but fun.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
NYT-11-20-98 1615EST &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
