<DOCNO> NYT19981125.0097 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-25 11:18 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8870 &Cx1f; taf-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-MARRIED-CATHOLIC-CLER     11-25 0886
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MARRIED-CATHOLIC-CLERGY-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A CATHOLIC BISHOP COURAGEOUSLY CALLS FOR 'MARRIED CLERGY' 
</HEADLINE>
   (Commentary)  
 &HT;    
 &HT;    (Mike McManus is a syndicated columnist whose ``Ethics &AMP;
Religion'' appears in almost 100 newspapers)
 &HT;    
 &HT;    (To purchase this ``separate buy'' article from the New York
Times Syndicate please contact syndicate sales representative NIRDI
RELIS in New York at (800) 972-3550 or (212) 499-3333, or fax her
at (212) 499-3382.)  
 &HT;    
 By MIKE McMANUS  
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features)  
 &HT;    
 &HT;    In a thoughtful pastoral letter published by his diocesan
newspaper, Catholic Bishop Raymond Lucker of New Ulm, Minn., has
