   4. ``CYBERLAW JOURNAL: ANTI-PORN LAW ENTERS COURT; DELAY
FOLLOWS''
</P>
<P>
   A host of civil rights groups and Web site owners argued at a
special hearing in a federal court in Philadelphia that a number of
online magazines, Web sites, and cyberspace enterprises could be in
violation of a new Internet censorship law. Later in the day, it
seemed their concerns had been heeded as a federal judge
temporarily blocked enforcement of the measure.
</P>
