   FBC-CHAMPBAILEY _ The Georgia Tech game was Champ Bailey's
coming-out party last season. Bailey was noted for his play at
cornerback, but he had several key receptions on offense that
helped the Bulldogs to a 27-24 victory. As the Tech game approaches
this season, Bailey has developed into one of the top two-way
players in the nation, leading the team in receptions and
interceptions. The game could be the final home game for Bailey, a
junior who is expected to turn pro next season. (Schlabach, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-BOHLS-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ In what should be the biggest
no-brainer since Playboy chose to feature Katarina Witt over Dick
Button, the University of Texas should announce this week that it
is retiring Ricky Williams' No. 34. (Bohls, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-UT-RECORD _ AUSTIN, Texas _ UT officials planned Monday for
a Ricky Williams celebration, figuring that he likely will rush for
the 63 yards he needs to break Tony Dorsett's career rushing record
of 6,082. Don't expect the game to be stopped when Williams gets
the record. (Halliburton, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-UT-RENFRO _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Dusty Renfro shows
determination, good attitude. A profile of the Texas A&AMP;M player.
(Wangrin, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-SECREPORT _ SEC Report. Capsules on the 11 SEC schools,
excluding Georgia. (Barnhart/ Parker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-ACCREPORT _ ACC Report. Capsules on the eight ACC schools,
excluding Georgia Tech. (Arey/Barnhart, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-BLACK-NOTES _ Black college notebook. (Reese, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   Thr following items are budgeted for Friday, November 27, 1998.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-VERMEIL _ When the three old codgers, Dan Reeves, Mike Ditka
and Dick Vermeil, returned to coaching two years ago, people
wondered if they'd be able to handle the changing face of the NFL.
Vermeil is struggling. After leaving the profession 15 or so years
ago because of burnout, he's facing those same demons while
coaching the Rams, Atlanta's Sunday opponent. In short, Vermeil
looks stressed, frustrated and sick. (Pasquarelli, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NFLBEST _ Highlights from upcoming NFL weekend.
(Pasquarelli, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GA-GATECH _ Matchup story on Georgia Tech's running game vs.
Georgia's run defense. Another one of the keys to the
Georgia-Georgia Tech game will be Tech's running game against the
Georgia defense. Tech has been ranked among the conference leaders
in rushing throughout the season with Joe Hamilton effectively
running the option. Georgia's defense is allowing more than 130
rushing yards per game, and Tech hope to exploit that weakness in
Saturday's game. (Rogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-BAYOU _ Eddie Robinson is no longer coaching at Grambling,
but the event he helped to begin will carry on this weekend in New
Orleans. The Bayou Classic, featuring Grambling and Southern, is
expected to attract more than 70,000 fans to the Louisiana
Superdome to watch a new era of Grambling football led by Doug
Williams, the former Tiger player and Super Bowl MVP. (Reese,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
