   COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   FBC-QUINCYCARTER _ Quincy Carter's initial signing with Georgia
Tech and eventual move to Georgia has been well-documented, but his
decision will be the topic of discussion this week as Georgia and
Georgia Tech prepare to meet in Athens. Carter has been one of the
key players for Georgia this season, and the Bulldogs might not
have a winning season without the freshman at quarterback.
Meanwhile, Tech has continued to succeed behind junior QB Joe
Hamilton. We will attempt to talk to players on both sides about
Carter's impact at Georgia, any hard feelings from Tech players,
etc. (Rogers/Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-COLLEGE-NOTES _ Inside Colleges notebook. (Barnhart, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-FORTVALLEY _ Fort Valley is making its first playoff
appearance in 13 years and the Wildcats began the playoffs on a
positive note last week with a 21-14 victory at Delta State. Next
up for Fort Valley is Carson-Newman, which is making its sixth
straight playoff appearance. (Reese, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
14.
</P>
