<P>
   FLA-FIELDHOCKEY _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Ron Hayes trumpets the
arrival of field hockey to the south Florida area. (Hayes, Palm
Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-LASTPLAY _ It has been a long year for Georgia Tech
cornerback Kofi Smith. He was the defender on Georgia's winning
touchdown pass in last season's 27-24 victory over Tech, and he
remembers the sequence of events as if it happened yesterday. Smith
had a difficult time accepting the loss and even contemplated
transferring to avoid facing fellow students and fans after getting
beat by UGA's Corey Allen for the touchdown. Smith has been an
important part of Tech's success this season, but is still haunted
by last year's game. He hopes for redemption Saturday against the
Bulldogs in Athens. (Rogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
WITH PHOTOS (mug of smith and action shot of last year's play).
MOVED.
</P>
