</P>
<P>
   VERMONT-WOOD-STOVES (Berlin, Vt.) _ In winters past, Molly
Prescott recalled, when her daughters came in from playing
outdoors, they would bake their mittens dry next to the woodstove
that long heated the family house in the rural Vermont hamlet of
Fletcher. But the Prescott girls are grown now. And for Mrs.
Prescott, a native Vermonter, ``the romance of the stove kind of
faded.'' By Carey Goldberg.
</P>
