worth its weight in gold.'' He says Friedan exemplifies how people
are increasingly growing older with vigor.
</P>
<P>
   Friedan's daughter, Emily, a pediatrician in Williamsville,
N.Y., said her mother always had an immense amount of energy, but _
referring to her mother's frenetic schedule _ adds: ``Some of us
think she's running, that she's trying to keep one step ahead of
the grim reaper.''
</P>
<P>
   Divorced for nearly three decades, she has two other grown
children, Jonathan an engineer in Philadelphia, and Daniel, a
Rutgers University physicist in Princeton, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   Friedan goes out to lunch and dinner almost every day she's at
home in Washington, and she often attends social events or lectures
at clubs where she is a member, such as the Cosmos Club, the Arts
Club of Washington or the National Press Club.
</P>
<P>
   A small woman with wispy white-grey hair and a penchant for
offbeat clothing, she is often approached by middle-aged or elderly
strangers who stop to thank her for her role in the feminist
movement.
</P>
<P>
   While she doesn't cook, she is apt to invite friends over for
cocktails in her dining room, where she keeps a well-stocked bar on
a large mirrored antique sideboard.
</P>
<P>
   Friedan is a die-hard fan of President Clinton, and praises him
for policies that have helped women, such as expanding the earned
income tax credit for lower income families so they can use the
money for child care.
</P>
<P>
   These days, in her lectures and writing, she is casting out
broad intellectual nets in search of solutions to the dilemma of
how to strike a better balance between work and family.
</P>
<P>
   She has been cautious to include men as well as women in her
discussions of how to lighten the parenting load on working
mothers.
</P>
<P>
   ``A person with her history and visibility is capable of drawing
attention to ideas and can really exert influence,'' said William
Galston, a fellow at the Brookings Institution, a Washington think
tank. ``She is playing a leading role in a policy game.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
