<HEADLINE>
SITE-SEEING: PEOPLE FINDERS 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   There are many people finders. Here are some free sites:
</P>
<P>
   SWITCHBOARD: www.switchboard.com
</P>
<P>
   Database: 120 million listings. Uses Info USA. Includes: e-mail
addresses and a knock-knock button, which is used to find out
whether listed people want to receive mail from searchers. Alta
Vista also uses Switchboard. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   INFOSPACE: www.infospace.com &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Database: 100 million in United States, 200 million in Europe;
16 million American yellow-page listings. Includes reverse
directory, fax numbers, e-mail, partial name searches, European
listings. Metacrawler, 555-1212, MSN, Netscape and America Online
use Infospace. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LYCOS: www.lycos.com &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Database: more than 90 million phone listings in the United
States. Uses Whowhere. Includes E-mail addresses, allows searches
by partial spelling. Used by MCI, US West Dex, Ziff-Davis and
Mindspring. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ANYWHO: www.anywho.com &QL;
</P>
<P>
   More than 90 million consumer listings in the United States.
Includes reverse directory, direct phone connections, partial name
searching, Web addresses, fax and toll-free numbers. Used by
Excite, Webcrawler and Infoseek. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (italics)The following people-finder sites charge for
searches:(end italics) &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   KNOWX: www.knowx.com &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Some searches are free, but costs range up to $65. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LOCATEME: www.locateme.com &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Can search more than 120 million records. Cost: $20 to $30. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1-800-U.S. SEARCH: www.1800ussearch.com &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Searches for people and does background checks. Cost: $79.95 for
finding people. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PEOPLE FINDER: www.people-finder.com &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Access to two billion public records. If you get a match, a name
search is $39.95. &QL;
</P>
