 &HT;    Tuberville appears Auburn-bound
 &HT;    By Tony Barnhart
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ What would Thanksgiving dinner be without a big
helping of coaching speculation? Here's the latest to enjoy with
your turkey and dressing:
</P>
<P>
   _ Barring some last-minute problem in putting together the deal,
Tommy Tuberville will be named the next coach at Auburn on Friday
or Saturday. He has been telling his coaching buddies around the
country that he's going and has even called some of them for advice
on drawing up his next contract. Tuberville has been trying to keep
quiet in order to get through tonight's game against Mississippi
State on ESPN. He hasn't succeeded. If the deal with Tuberville
breaks down, Bobby Wallace of Temple is the second choice. Wallace,
who went to Mississippi State, will be on the Ole Miss candidate
list if Tuberville leaves.
</P>
<P>
   _ Tulane coach Tommy Bowden has sent word through friends that
he wants the Clemson job. Tulane will come back with a strong offer
and might invoke a $750,000 buyout clause in Bowden's contract,
which kicks in if the school draws up plans for specific facility
improvements. Clemson might have to pay a lot to get Bowden, whose
team plays its last game against Louisiana Tech tonight. Bowden
could interview as early as Friday. But our Big East contacts tell
us not to count out Virginia Tech's Frank Beamer. He's more ``old
school,'' which might be a more comfortable fit for some of the
older fans.
</P>
<P>
   _ Florida defensive coordinator Bobby Stoops was expected to
interview for the Oklahoma job Wednesday and then take his family
to spend Thanksgiving day with Florida coach Steve Spurrier and his
family. Stoops, who also is on Iowa's list, has told friends that
he is considering Oklahoma because he believes the opportunity to
win there will come quicker.
</P>
<P>
   _ Tennessee offensive coordinator David Cutcliffe is the leading
candidate to become the next head coach at Middle Tennessee State.
Cutcliffe was interested in the Kentucky job when the Wildcats
hired Hal Mumme two years ago.Phillip Fulmer
</P>
<P>
   _ Alabama could lose quarterbacks coach Charlie StubbsJeff
HortonNeil Callaway
</P>
