   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BETTY-FRIEDAN (Washington) _ As the grande dame of feminism,
Betty Friedan helped lead women into a work world of better pay,
equal access to jobs, education and promotions. Now, at 77, this
grandmother of seven says child care is the next challenge for
women. Feminists ``will not be able to declare victory until the
raising of children is seen equally as a man's responsibility as
well as a woman's,'' she declared. By JUDY HOLLAND. (Already
filed.)
</P>
