   (NYT30) NEW YORK -- Nov. 25, 1998 -- MARIJUANA-ADVOCATE, 11-25
-- Lynn Zimmer, 51, is a sociologist and a passionate advocate of
decriminalizing marijuana. Her arguments about marijuana's
essential harmlessness have been collected in a recent book
(co-written with Dr. John Morgan) called ``Marijuana Myths,
Marijuana Facts,'' and have become a flashpoint in the battle over
legalization. (Chester Higgins Jr./New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT29) MACON, Ga. -- Nov. 25, 1998 -- GA-BATTLEFIELD-PARK,
11-25 -- The Griswoldville battlefield in Macon, where a
Confederate militia of old men and boys suffered heavy casualties
at the hands of Gen. William Sherman, has been dedicated by Georgia
as a state historic site. Encroaching development had threatened to
swallow the site until history buffs and others raised much of the
$95,000 needed to buy and preserve the land. (Alan S. Weiner/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
