<P>
   (NYT25) UNDATED -- Nov. 25, 1998 -- MEXICO-DRUGS, 11-25 -- In a
secret July 1997 report to federal prosecutors, made availabe to
the New York Times, the director of Mexico's anti-drug police
claims that several tons of illicit drugs are smuggled to the U.S.
per week from the Mexican state of Quintana Roo. The officer's
report identifies the smuggler in charge in the state as Ramon
Alcides Magana, seen in this undated photo. (New York Times Photo)
</P>
