Leventhal, a promoter of Arlo Guthrie. Pushing 80, Leventhal
remains a living history of 20th-century music from the big-band
era through the folk revival, when he managed or promoted concerts
for such artists as the Weavers, Pete Seeger, Judy Collins and Joan
Baez. ``I never felt comfortable in the rock world,'' he says.
``The behavior. The whole scene. It wasn't my style.'' (Sara
Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT17) UNDATED -- Nov. 25, 1998 -- HOME-IMPROVEMENT-B&AMP;W, 11-25
-- Can anything be done to improve the efficiency of the average
home fireplace? One possibility is to add inserts that convert the
fireplace into a stove. Wood-burning inserts fit in the fireplace
and use the existing chimney to exhaust smoke and combustion gases.
They have faceplates with metal or glass doors that fit across the
fireplace opening to enclose the fire. (Edward R. Lipinski/New York
Times Illustration) *LITE
