r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-COWBOYS-NOTES-TEX     11-25 0459
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-NOTES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GAILEY EXPECTED TO MAKE GAME-TIME DECISION ON SANDERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN LYONS and CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ When the Cowboys meet the Minnesota Vikings
today, Dallas will be trying to clinch its first playoff berth in
two seasons. As Chan Gailey rises this morning, he remains unsure
if he'll have Deion Sanders on defense.
</P>
<P>
   Sanders did not have his sprained, left big toe in a walking
cast, but instead sported tennis shoes as he walked around the
club's jogging track yesterday, talking with team owner Jerry Jones
and trainer Jim Maurer.
</P>
<P>
   Sanders' status, and that of backup running back Chris Warren
(groin) won't be determined until before kickoff.
</P>
<P>
   ``How active or inactive they'll be won't be determined until
closer to game time,'' Gailey said.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, Gailey said he was unaware the Cowboys could clinch a
playoff berth this soon. But according to the league, the Cowboys
make the playoffs if they win ``and'' Arizona and New Orleans lose
on Sunday. The Cardinals are at Kansas City; the Saints are at
Miami.
Kick return duties
</P>
<P>
   Gailey has settled on wide receiver Jeff Ogden to replace Warren
on kickoff returns, and cornerback Kevin Smith to replace Sanders
on punt returns.
</P>
<P>
   Smith has one punt return in his pro career for 17 yards in
1992.
</P>
<P>
   ``The key thing for me is to make sure I catch the ball,'' Smith
said. ``But hey, I plan on doing something with it when I get it.
Deion has kidded me a lot about it this week.''
</P>
<P>
   Ogden said he didn't return kicks in college or high school.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm just going to hit the holes and run as fast as I can,''
Ogden said.
Stopping Moss
</P>
<P>
   Smith said the key to defending Vikings wide receivers Randy
Moss and Cris Carter is not solely in tight coverage.
</P>
<P>
   ``Me and Charlie \RWilliams\S have to make sure we make plays on
the ball,'' Smith said. ``A lot of times, when you are in coverage
and on top of the guys, they can still jump up and get the ball
over you. Being in coverage is not enough.''
</P>
<P>
   Williams said he's aware of Moss' jumping ability. But, ``we
also got to hit those guys if they get the ball. We've got to be
physical.''
Jerry speak
</P>
<P>
   Jones compared the pregame buzz to a ``Texas-Oklahoma game.''
But what Jones really likes is the Cowboys are a legitimate part of
the ``aura'' of a big game again. He doesn't even mind his team is
considered the underdog.
</P>
<P>
   ``I like that,'' Jones said. ``It's just like the entire year. I
enjoy being unexpectedly competitive _ unlike the years when
everybody gave us the Super Bowl before the season. It's more fun
to be a part of a team and do what I do if we are challenged by
doing the unexpected.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
