<P>
   NY-TUXEDO-PARK (Tuxedo Park, N.Y.) _ It is difficult to
reconcile the watercolor renderings of pert Dutch-roofed houses and
sprawling Tudor apartment complexes with the rocky forest that
rings the very private enclave of Tuxedo Park. But if developers
and town officials have their way _ and it appears they are close _
Tuxedo, with its population of 3,000, may quadruple in size over
the next decade. By Tracie Rozhon.
</P>
<P>
   PHONE-SOUNDS (Undated) _ Telephones used to be more predictable.
They were generally tethered securely to a wall, and when they
rang, well, they rang. Lately the cunning little mobile phones that
people like to carry _ the ones that also send e-mail and receive
stock-market quotations _ have been emitting more elaborate sounds.
By Karrie Jacobs.
</P>
<P>
   KID-COLLECTORS (Undated) _ Josephine Bradlee, 9, doesn't know
any other girl who collects basketball cards, which is a point of
pride with her. ``Pretty much every kid I know collects
something,'' she said. Her twin sister, Beatrice, collects key
chains. Her brother, Marshall, 6, dabbles in Matchbox cars. By Kim
Stevens.
</P>
